          <!--
            Here's how a passive reference may look like:

            "NeuRIS Modeling"
              * We have a single, generic reference element (+ schema) that is standardized across streams in order to reduce the number of variants that we and our users need to understand

            "Portal requirements"
              * We provide all data that the portal needs for building a link to NeuRIS documents (type, document ID)
              * We support arbitrary URIs (for non-NeuRIS references)
              * We support plain text references (e.g. for non-NeuRIS references, also not yet in NeuRIS)
                * ‚ùì how is this different to incomplete references?

            "API user's requirements"
              * We provide data that a client can use to download the source (without relying on the link built in the portal's UI)

            "Stream requirements"
              * We support all data that the streams need to have in their passive references
              * The stream's requirements may overlap, but all the "metadata" fields will be optional in the schema

            "LDML Harmonization"
              * We use German node names
              * Each node has a domainTerm for the human reader
              * Each field's data is encoded as a value of a child element (not via attributes)
              * We're staying in the LDML standard's <akn:otherReferences> and <akn:implicitReferences> elements and we're using a custom <ris:reference> for the actual data
                * ‚ùì LDML's implicitReference is maybe not meant to be referenced from within a reference (but it may be the only place where we can put "arbitrary" custom data on references
                  * ‚ùì LDML's <references> <activeRef> <passiveRef> -> could we use these?
                  * ‚ùì "analysys" may be a place for "inferred/implicit" information, not made explicit in the document

            "Additional rules on the XML"
              * We don't add (parent node) context information to the node name, but error on the side of simple node names.
                * <reference></dokumentnummer></reference> is good enough information for not taking </dokumentnummer> for the current document's number
          -->
